{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-object-template-js","path":"/exhibition/labels/study-of-hands-thomas-lawrence/","result":{"data":{"directusHumantouch":{"title":"Lightness of touch","description":"<p>Self-taught, Thomas Lawrence was an instinctive draughtsman, who went on to become President of the Royal Academy. He understood the importance of gesture in communicating character and in introducing a sense of movement in portraits.&nbsp; Gently folding as they pick up a thread or piece of fabric, these hands convey the grace, delicacy and sensitivity of the unknown female sitter.</p>\n<p>Thomas Lawrence (1769&ndash;1830)<br />Study of hands<br />Date unknown<br />Red and black chalks on paper, <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">11.5 x 25.9 cm</span><br />Given by the Friends of the Fitzwilliam Museum, 1972<br />PD.39-1972</p>","slug":"study-of-hands-thomas-lawrence","section":"Three","section_name":"hands-at-work","hero_image":{"id":1768,"data":{"full_url":"https://fitz-cms-images.s3.eu-west-2.amazonaws.com/pd.39-1972_1_202002_kly25_dc1sd.jpg","thumbnails":[{"url":"https://content.fitz.ms/fitz-website/assets/PD.39-1972_1_202002_kly25_dc1SD.jpg?key=directus-small-crop","dimension":"64x64","width":64,"height":64},{"url":"https://content.fitz.ms/fitz-website/assets/PD.39-1972_1_202002_kly25_dc1SD.jpg?key=directus-small-contain","dimension":"64x64","width":64,"height":64},{"url":"https://content.fitz.ms/fitz-website/assets/PD.39-1972_1_202002_kly25_dc1SD.jpg?key=directus-medium-crop","dimension":"300x300","width":300,"height":300},{"url":"https://content.fitz.ms/fitz-website/assets/PD.39-1972_1_202002_kly25_dc1SD.jpg?key=directus-medium-contain","dimension":"300x300","width":300,"height":300},{"url":"https://content.fitz.ms/fitz-website/assets/PD.39-1972_1_202002_kly25_dc1SD.jpg?key=directus-large-crop","dimension":"800x600","width":800,"height":600},{"url":"https://content.fitz.ms/fitz-website/assets/PD.39-1972_1_202002_kly25_dc1SD.jpg?key=directus-large-